 experiments. In this algorithm, you choose an element in the array as the pivot element. Then you rearrange all the other elements in the array such that all the elements less than the pivot element are placed to its left and all the elements greater than the pivot element are placed to its right. This process is then repeated for the left and right subarrays until the entire array is sorted. Here is an example of quicksort algorithm in C# code:
<jupyter_code>
def quicksort(arr):
  if len(arr) <= 1:
    return arr
  else:
    pivot = arr[0]
    left = []
    right = []
    for i in range(1, len(arr)):
      if arr[i] < pivot:
        left.append(arr[i])
      else:
        right.append(arr[i])
    return quicksort(left) + [pivot] + quicksort(right)
